  "prompt": "How can I get the HTML/CSS/JavaScript source code of a website?",
  "response": "Here are several ways to view a website's source code:\n\n1. Browser Developer Tools (Recommended)\n- Right-click on the webpage and select \"Inspect\" or \"View Page Source\"\n- Press Ctrl+U (Windows/Linux) or Cmd+U (Mac)\n- Use keyboard shortcut F12 or Ctrl+Shift+I\n\n2. View Source\n- Right-click and select \"View Page Source\"\n- Shows raw HTML\n\n3. Browser Extensions\n- Web Developer Chrome/Firefox extensions\n- \"View Source\" browser add-ons\n\n4. Online Tools\n- View Source websites\n- Web archive services\n\n5. Command Line\n- curl website.com\n- wget -O- website.com\n\n6. Browser Options\n- Chrome: View > Developer > View Source\n- Firefox: Tools > Web Developer > Page Source\n\n7. Save Entire Webpage\n- File > Save Page As\n- Saves HTML, CSS, and associated files\n\n8. Using Browser's Network Tab\n- Open Developer Tools\n- Go to Network tab\n- Reload page\n- Inspect individual resource files\n\n9. JavaScript Console\n- Open Developer Tools\n- Console tab can reveal scripts\n\nRemember: Some websites may have complex or minified code, and dynamic content might require additional investigation.",
